@storymaniac you need to seriously start researching this topic so your opinions and judgments are solidly based on science and logic. You do not have a shred of evidence virus can work or spread they way it is claimed. It is known people had unusual breathing problems this year. If you had seen and read the reports I have, you would be aware that some postmortem showed people had their lungs destroyed in a way similar to an instant exposure to 10 000 feet altitude. Experienced medical doctors know of no way any virus can ever do such extreme damage to human lungs. Furthermore you should know such effect might be related to a situation where normal atmosphere loses its normal oxygen level. Going a step further it should be pointed that emitting 60 GHz radio wave could break down oxygen molecules in the atmosphere possibly making it harder for the body to obtain oxygen into its blood.

I cannot understand how your suggestion makes sense and why would people not following it be 'assholes'. Why don't you wear gloves and a very tight builders or altitude mask if you are concerned?     

Using some untested method against an invisible unidentified enemy doesn't sound like a likely victory. Lot's of paranoia though. Maybe people should consider paying attention if there are some locations where it is harder to breathe for many people?
